# Gripp SDK for PHP

This is a PHP SDK (`codebes/gripp-sdk`) for the Gripp business management JSON-RPC API.

## Project Structure

```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ GrippClient.php                  # Static facade - configure token/URL here first
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Transport/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ JsonRpcClient.php            # HTTP transport (batch, pagination, retries)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ JsonRpcResponse.php          # Response wrapper (rows, count, toCollection)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Query/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ QueryBuilder.php             # Fluent filter builder (where/orderBy/limit/get)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Filter.php                   # Filter value object (field, operator, value)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Resources/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Resource.php                 # Abstract base class - all 54 resources extend this
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Concerns/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ CanRead.php              # get(), find(), all(), where(), first()
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ CanCreate.php            # create()
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ CanUpdate.php            # update()
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ CanDelete.php            # delete()
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [54 resource classes]        # Company, Contact, Project, Invoice, etc.
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Exceptions/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ GrippException.php           # Base exception
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ AuthenticationException.php  # 401/403
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ RateLimitException.php       # 429
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ RequestException.php         # Other API errors
```

## Key Patterns

- **Always call `GrippClient::configure()` before using any resource.** It reads from `GRIPP_API_TOKEN` env var if no arguments are given. Uses `https://api.gripp.com` by default; override with `GRIPP_API_URL` env var or `baseUrl` parameter.
- **Resources are static classes.** Usage: `Company::find(123)`, `Company::create([...])`, `Project::where('name', 'contains', 'foo')->get()`.
- **Traits compose CRUD capabilities.** Check which traits a resource `use`s to know what operations are available. Some resources are read-only (e.g. `Cost`, `File`, `Memorial`).
- **Each resource has schema constants:** `FIELDS` (field‚Üítype), `READONLY`, `REQUIRED`, `RELATIONS` (FK‚Üíclass).
- **JSON-RPC methods follow the pattern:** `{entity}.{action}` (e.g. `company.get`, `project.create`).
- **The `Notification` resource is special** - it uses `emit()` and `emitall()` instead of standard CRUD.
- **QueryBuilder auto-paginates.** `get()` fetches all pages automatically. Use `limit()` to restrict to a single page.
- **QueryBuilder auto-prefixes entity names.** `Project::where('createdon', ...)` becomes `project.createdon` automatically.
- **Date helpers on QueryBuilder:** `whereDateBetween()`, `whereYear()`, `whereMonth()`, `whereModifiedSince()`.
- **Transport hooks:** `beforeRequest(callback)` fires before each HTTP call. `onRateLimitExceeded(callback)` fires on 429/503-1004.
- **Rate limit tracking:** `getRateLimitRemaining()` and `getRateLimitLimit()` on the transport.
- **503 with error_code 1004** is treated as a rate limit (Gripp's short-burst throttle).

## Filter Operators

When using `where($field, $operator, $value)`:

equals, notequals, contains, notcontains, startswith, endswith, greaterthan, lessthan, greaterequals, lessequals, in, notin, isnull, isnotnull

Two-argument `where($field, $value)` defaults to `equals`.

**Important:** The Gripp API uses `greaterequals` / `lessequals` (NOT `greaterthanorequal` / `lessthanorequal`).

## Usage Examples

```php
// Configure the client (required before any API call)
GrippClient::configure('token');

// Find by ID
$company = Company::find(123);

// Query with filters
$projects = Project::where('name', 'contains', 'Website')
    ->where('archived', false)
    ->orderBy('createdon', 'desc')
    ->limit(25)
    ->get(); // Returns Illuminate\Support\Collection

// Create
$result = Company::create(['companyname' => 'Acme', 'relationtype' => 'COMPANY']);

// Update
Company::update(123, ['phone' => '+31201234567']);

// Delete
Company::delete(123);

// Batch operations
$transport = GrippClient::getTransport();
$transport->startBatch();
Company::find(1);
Company::find(2);
$responses = $transport->executeBatch();
```

## Development

```bash
composer install
vendor/bin/phpunit          # Run tests
vendor/bin/gripp-setup      # Interactive credential setup
```

## Coding Conventions

- PSR-4 autoloading under `CodeBes\GrippSdk\`
- PHP 8.1+ features (named arguments, match expressions, union types)
- Static methods on all resources (no instantiation needed)
- Returns `Illuminate\Support\Collection` for multi-record queries, `?array` for single records
- Entity names are lowercase concatenation of class name: `ProjectPhase` ‚Üí `'projectphase'`
- Fields use the Gripp API naming conventions (lowercase, no underscores between words in entity names)

## Resource Capabilities Reference

**Full CRUD:** AbsenceRequest, AbsenceRequestLine, BulkPrice, CalendarItem, Company, CompanyDossier, Contact, Contract, ContractLine, CostHeading, Department, Employee, EmployeeFamily, EmploymentContract, ExternalLink, Hour, Invoice, InvoiceLine, Ledger, Offer, OfferPhase, OfferProjectLine, Packet, PacketLine, Payment, PriceException, Product, Project, ProjectPhase, PurchaseInvoice, PurchaseInvoiceLine, PurchaseOrder, PurchaseOrderLine, PurchasePayment, RejectionReason, Tag, Task, TaskPhase, TaskType, TimelineEntry, Unit, Webhook

**Create + Read + Update (no delete):** EmployeeYearlyLeaveBudget, UmbrellaProject

**Read-only:** Cost, EmployeeTarget, File, Memorial, MemorialLine, RevenueTarget, YearTarget, YearTargetType

**Custom methods only:** Notification (emit, emitall)
